# Stimulants
addiction-Stimulants-onset = Your pulse quickens. You feel sharper than usual.
addiction-Stimulants-recovery = Your heart settles. The edge fades.

addiction-stimulants-hint-1 = Your heart is beating a little fast.
addiction-stimulants-hint-2 = Your hands won't stay still.
addiction-stimulants-hint-3 = Pressure builds behind your sternum.
addiction-stimulants-hint-4 = Your muscles keep tensing on their own.
addiction-stimulants-hint-5 = Vision flickers at the edges.
addiction-stimulants-hint-6 = Your legs won't hold you properly.

addiction-stimulants-withdrawal-1 = Everything feels sluggish without it.
addiction-stimulants-withdrawal-2 = You can barely keep your eyes open.
addiction-stimulants-withdrawal-3 = Cold sweat soaks through your clothes.
addiction-stimulants-withdrawal-4 = The floor looks close. Very close.
addiction-stimulants-withdrawal-5 = Darkness creeps in from the edges.

# Desoxyephedrine
addiction-Desoxyephedrine-onset = Something behind your eyes ignites.
addiction-Desoxyephedrine-recovery = The tension bleeds out. You feel almost calm.

addiction-desoxy-hint-1 = You feel irritable for no reason.
addiction-desoxy-hint-2 = The urge to break something is hard to ignore.
addiction-desoxy-hint-3 = You're sure someone's watching. You check again.
addiction-desoxy-hint-4 = Did that shadow just move?
addiction-desoxy-hint-5 = Blind spots flare and vanish.
addiction-desoxy-hint-6 = Your grip on things keeps slipping.

addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-1 = Your skin crawls like something is under it.
addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-2 = You feel hollow. Wrong.
addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-3 = The crash hits all at once.
addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-4 = You're soaked. The room tilts.
addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-5 = Your body refuses to cooperate.
addiction-desoxy-withdrawal-6 = You can't take much more of this.

# SpaceDrugs
addiction-SpaceDrugs-onset = The world brightens. Everything hums.
addiction-SpaceDrugs-recovery = Reality settles back. Colors lose their shine.

addiction-spacedrugs-hint-1 = You feel like you're drifting slightly above the floor.
addiction-spacedrugs-hint-2 = The colors around you seem too vivid.
addiction-spacedrugs-hint-3 = The walls seem to breathe if you look too long.
addiction-spacedrugs-hint-4 = You almost hear the light.
addiction-spacedrugs-hint-5 = Darkness gathers at the edges of your vision.
addiction-spacedrugs-hint-6 = The room dissolves a little.

addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-1 = Everything feels flat and grey.
addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-2 = The hum is gone. The silence is too loud.
addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-3 = Nothing feels real anymore. Or maybe it's too real.
addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-4 = You keep looking for something that isn't there.
addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-5 = Reality won't hold still.
addiction-spacedrugs-withdrawal-6 = You can't tell where you end and the room begins.

# Ephedrine
addiction-Ephedrine-onset = Your chest tightens. Energy floods through you.
addiction-Ephedrine-recovery = Your breathing steadies. Your body feels its own again.

addiction-ephedrine-hint-1 = Your hands tremble slightly.
addiction-ephedrine-hint-2 = Something to take the edge off would help.
addiction-ephedrine-hint-3 = Your heart is working harder than it should.
addiction-ephedrine-hint-4 = Everything moves so slow without it.
addiction-ephedrine-hint-5 = You're sweating and shaking. You want more.
addiction-ephedrine-hint-6 = Vision smears. The craving is unbearable.

addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-1 = Your chest feels tight for no reason.
addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-2 = Breathing takes more effort than it should.
addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-3 = Your lungs feel like they've forgotten the rhythm.
addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-4 = A deep exhaustion settles into your bones.
addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-5 = You gasp. Air doesn't come fast enough.
addiction-ephedrine-withdrawal-6 = Your body is shutting down the parts it doesn't need.

# Nicotine
addiction-Nicotine-onset = You feel a faint restlessness settle in.
addiction-Nicotine-recovery = The irritability passes. You breathe a little easier.

addiction-nicotine-hint-1 = You need something to do with your hands.
addiction-nicotine-hint-2 = Something familiar is missing.
addiction-nicotine-hint-3 = Your mouth is dry.
addiction-nicotine-hint-4 = Everything is getting on your nerves.
addiction-nicotine-hint-5 = You can't focus on anything.
addiction-nicotine-hint-6 = Your nerves feel raw.

addiction-nicotine-withdrawal-1 = The restlessness is getting harder to sit with.
addiction-nicotine-withdrawal-2 = Your hands keep reaching for something that isn't there.
addiction-nicotine-withdrawal-3 = You're snapping at everything. You know why.
addiction-nicotine-withdrawal-4 = Your head throbs dully.
addiction-nicotine-withdrawal-5 = The irritation has become a constant hum.

# Fentanyl
addiction-Fentanyl-onset = A warm numbness spreads through you. Everything softens.
addiction-Fentanyl-recovery = The weight lifts. Your body remembers how to feel again.

addiction-fentanyl-hint-1 = The pain is coming back. You notice it more than you should.
addiction-fentanyl-hint-2 = Something feels off. You keep thinking about how good it felt.
addiction-fentanyl-hint-3 = The warmth doesn't last as long anymore.
addiction-fentanyl-hint-4 = You need more just to feel normal.
addiction-fentanyl-hint-5 = Your body aches in places you forgot could hurt.
addiction-fentanyl-hint-6 = Nothing works right without it.

addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-1 = Your skin feels raw. Everything is too sharp.
addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-2 = Cold sweats. The warmth is completely gone.
addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-3 = Your muscles cramp. You can't get comfortable.
addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-4 = Your stomach turns. The pain is everywhere.
addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-5 = You can barely breathe through it.
addiction-fentanyl-withdrawal-6 = Your body is tearing itself apart looking for relief.

reagent-effect-naloxone-withdrawal = Something violently reverses in your body.
